> In addition to careful balancing and CCing the combustion chambers,
> what else would contribute to smoothness and quietness of a running
> VW engine.

Multiport electronic fuel injection, for more even mixture distribution,
and electronic ignition, for a hotter spark.  Maybe even a
distributorless electronic ignition for hotter sparks at the right time
consistently.  Wolfsburg, Munich, Detroit, and Tokyo can't *all* be
wrong on this.  :)

